WEBVTT

00:06.173 --> 00:09.176
[pensive instrumental music]

00:09.176 --> 00:16.183
♪ ♪

00:23.065 --> 00:26.110
[woman singing in Norwegian]

00:26.110 --> 00:33.117
♪ ♪

00:45.796 --> 00:52.803
♪ ♪

01:19.330 --> 01:22.333
[waves whooshing]

01:27.922 --> 01:30.925
[soft indistinct chatter]

01:30.925 --> 01:32.927
[woman coughing]

01:58.244 --> 01:59.995
[woman coughing]

02:01.956 --> 02:04.959
[indistinct chatter continues]

02:23.561 --> 02:25.062
Hey! Hey!

02:25.062 --> 02:26.397
[child grunting]

02:26.397 --> 02:28.524
Stop.
Stop.

02:28.524 --> 02:30.943
There's enough for all of us.

02:30.943 --> 02:33.904
[soft dramatic music]

02:33.904 --> 02:36.907
♪ ♪

02:36.907 --> 02:39.243
[sighs]

02:39.243 --> 02:41.912
♪ ♪

02:41.912 --> 02:43.581
[Holden] Structure
seems to be holding.

02:43.581 --> 02:44.999
[Naomi] Good.

02:44.999 --> 02:46.208
[Holden] Water's
dripping through in places

02:46.208 --> 02:48.085
but not enough to be an issue.

02:48.085 --> 02:50.296
RCE and the Belters
set up separate camps,

02:50.296 --> 02:52.923
so not much
has really changed down here.

02:52.923 --> 02:54.425
Except they're gonna
hate each other even more.

02:54.425 --> 02:55.926
Except for that.

02:55.926 --> 02:59.555
Naomi, we got some daylight
peeking through.

02:59.555 --> 03:01.432
Water must've receded some.

03:01.432 --> 03:03.767
It has but not as quickly
as we hoped.

03:03.767 --> 03:06.979
Scopes are still showing
an ocean sitting on top of you.

03:06.979 --> 03:08.772
Nowhere at all for us to go?

03:08.772 --> 03:11.775
[Naomi] Not unless
you managed to pack a boat.

03:11.775 --> 03:14.194
So how long until
we get back to the surface?

03:14.194 --> 03:16.405
I can't tell for sure, but...

03:16.405 --> 03:18.407
not for a couple of days,
at least.

03:18.407 --> 03:22.077
Sounds like we're gonna
be down here for a while, then.

03:23.162 --> 03:25.414
Any progress getting
the drive back online?

03:25.414 --> 03:28.417
No, fusion doesn't
work here anymore.

03:28.417 --> 03:30.002
[Holden] Fucking Miller.

03:30.002 --> 03:32.046
How long
will the reserves last?

03:32.046 --> 03:33.756
Us and the Edward Israel

03:33.756 --> 03:36.884
can maintain orbit
for months on batteries, but...

03:36.884 --> 03:38.344
I ran the calculations

03:38.344 --> 03:41.472
on the Barb's
orbital decay rate.

03:41.472 --> 03:43.390
Based on the ship's
current altitude speed

03:43.390 --> 03:45.059
and power reserves,
they have

03:45.059 --> 03:46.810
maybe a few more days

03:46.810 --> 03:49.021
before they fall out of orbit.

03:49.021 --> 03:51.398
I need to come up
with something fast.

03:51.398 --> 03:54.777
Keep me updated
if anything changes.

03:54.777 --> 03:55.861
[woman coughing]

03:55.861 --> 03:57.488
Holden.

04:00.658 --> 04:02.201
Can we go back up
to the surface?

04:02.201 --> 04:03.535
Not yet.

04:03.535 --> 04:05.329
Water's receding
slower than we thought.

04:05.329 --> 04:07.665
We only have enough
water purification tablets

04:07.665 --> 04:10.751
to last a day, maybe two.

04:11.835 --> 04:14.213
We need to figure out a way
to send down a resupply.

04:14.213 --> 04:17.216
You saw what happened
to the RCE shuttle.

04:17.216 --> 04:18.968
Parachuting supplies
might be an option,

04:18.968 --> 04:20.719
but we still won't be able
to get to anything

04:20.719 --> 04:21.971
until the water recedes.

04:21.971 --> 04:23.681
Listen,
I'm doing everything I can.

04:23.681 --> 04:26.475
What can we do to help you?

04:26.475 --> 04:28.352
[scoffs]
So we're all just still

04:28.352 --> 04:30.646
at the mercy of you
and your invisible friend.

04:30.646 --> 04:37.653
♪ ♪

04:43.575 --> 04:46.578
[foreboding music]

04:46.578 --> 04:53.127
♪ ♪

04:53.127 --> 04:54.545
[Elvi] You said you started

04:54.545 --> 04:56.755
noticing the spots
about an hour ago?

04:56.755 --> 04:58.382
[Jakob] Yes.

04:58.382 --> 05:00.634
[indistinct chatter]

05:00.634 --> 05:03.012
- It's, uh...
- [device whirs]

05:03.012 --> 05:04.221
...it's in both eyes?

05:04.221 --> 05:06.098
It's worse in my left eye,

05:06.098 --> 05:08.100
but there's some
in my right eyes as well.

05:16.358 --> 05:18.068
My wife's a med tech.

05:18.068 --> 05:19.528
She mentioned she saw a child

05:19.528 --> 05:21.655
with a eye infection
a few days ago.

05:21.655 --> 05:23.657
Some kind of outbreak?

05:23.657 --> 05:26.326
Mm, no,
I wouldn't call it that.

05:26.326 --> 05:29.621
It's more like an allergic
reaction of some kind.

05:30.706 --> 05:32.791
So you can treat it?

05:32.791 --> 05:34.918
Antihistamine compound
should clear it up,

05:34.918 --> 05:37.671
but I...I need to check
everyone first to be sure.

05:37.671 --> 05:39.131
Just sit tight.

05:39.131 --> 05:45.220
♪ ♪

05:48.682 --> 05:50.809
[Murtry] The Edward Israel
can't tell us

05:50.809 --> 05:52.811
exactly how long
we're gonna be down here,

05:52.811 --> 05:55.481
so we're operating
as if indefinitely.

05:55.481 --> 05:56.732
What's our food and water
situation?

05:56.732 --> 05:58.567
Our purifiers are at 100%,

05:58.567 --> 06:00.277
and we have four and a half
cases of emergency rations.

06:00.277 --> 06:01.987
Good, I still want everyone

06:01.987 --> 06:05.616
on one food and water ration
per day till we know more.

06:05.616 --> 06:07.201
Belters are gonna
run out of food before us,

06:07.201 --> 06:08.827
and when they do,
they're gonna act desperate,

06:08.827 --> 06:10.662
so we need to be ready.

06:10.662 --> 06:12.414
I've already seen them
eyeballing our gear.

06:12.414 --> 06:14.166
Yeah, they jumped us once.
They're gonna do it again.

06:14.166 --> 06:15.834
Protect our camp
and our equipment at all costs.

06:15.834 --> 06:17.211
But be smart.

06:17.211 --> 06:18.921
We're outnumbered,

06:18.921 --> 06:20.672
and our tactical advantages
are diminished down here.

06:20.672 --> 06:23.258
There's a fight coming,
but let them bring it to us.

06:23.258 --> 06:24.676
[Murtry]
If everyone keeps their heads,

06:24.676 --> 06:26.512
we'll all make it out of here.

06:26.512 --> 06:27.805
You know what to do.

06:27.805 --> 06:29.056
Go do it.

06:31.517 --> 06:33.894
[sighs]

06:33.894 --> 06:40.901
♪ ♪

06:44.988 --> 06:47.699
Two days?
That's it?

06:47.699 --> 06:50.410
[Naomi] The Barb has maybe
a day of battery power left.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.287
After that,
it won't be able to accelerate

06:52.287 --> 06:53.997
and raise its orbit.

06:53.997 --> 06:55.874
There has to be
something we can do.

06:55.874 --> 06:58.627
We're going to reroute the
batteries on the light shuttles

06:58.627 --> 07:00.629
to power the Barb's thrusters.

07:00.629 --> 07:02.089
That will buy more time
in orbit.

07:02.089 --> 07:03.632
How much more time?

07:03.632 --> 07:05.300
I can't say exactly until
I see the power modules.

07:05.300 --> 07:07.094
Okay.

07:07.094 --> 07:09.179
- What else can we do?
[Alex] Here, take a look.

07:10.430 --> 07:11.557
All right...
[clears throat]

07:11.557 --> 07:13.809
...our best guess is that, um,

07:13.809 --> 07:15.853
this perimeter of moons
is the boundary

07:15.853 --> 07:18.021
for this fusion shutdown.

07:18.021 --> 07:21.400
We just won't know
until we are outside of them.

07:21.400 --> 07:23.819
- Is that where we're heading?
- Not yet.

07:23.819 --> 07:25.529
Only as a last resort.

07:25.529 --> 07:27.823
What do you mean, last resort?

07:27.823 --> 07:29.783
The Barb won't make it
that far on battery power.

07:29.783 --> 07:32.286
[stammers, sighs]

07:32.286 --> 07:34.580
If we got it, we're gonna
off-load your daughter

07:34.580 --> 07:36.957
and everyone else onto
the Roci, all right?

07:36.957 --> 07:39.001
Nobody on the Barb is gonna
go down with that ship.

07:39.001 --> 07:40.752
If we lose the lithium ore
that we mined,

07:40.752 --> 07:43.422
we may as well be dead.

07:43.422 --> 07:45.299
We'll have nothing left

07:45.299 --> 07:48.051
and no way
to rebuild the colony.

07:48.051 --> 07:50.345
Please, there has to be
something else.

07:50.345 --> 07:52.306
- It can't end like this.
[Naomi] I know.

07:52.306 --> 07:54.016
And we're doing
everything we can

07:54.016 --> 07:56.143
to make sure
that doesn't happen.

08:01.398 --> 08:04.693
[Avasarala] While this attempt
to attack Earth's defenses

08:04.693 --> 08:06.612
was easily deterred,

08:06.612 --> 08:09.531
it was not
as easily avoidable.

08:09.531 --> 08:12.159
We have a peace agreement
with the OPA,

08:12.159 --> 08:14.620
and I put my trust
in our new allies

08:14.620 --> 08:18.749
to provide justice for
the victims of the hijacking.

08:18.749 --> 08:22.711
The OPA leadership failed me,
and I, in turn,

08:22.711 --> 08:24.755
failed the people
of this planet

08:24.755 --> 08:27.132
by not putting
a high enough priority

08:27.132 --> 08:30.135
on bringing these terrorists
to justice.

08:31.720 --> 08:34.681
The safety of this planet
and its people

08:34.681 --> 08:37.100
is my sacred responsibility

08:37.100 --> 08:40.729
and one that I have
never taken lightly

08:40.729 --> 08:42.022
and never will.

08:42.022 --> 08:43.982
Jesus Christ.

08:43.982 --> 08:46.360
I sound incompetent!

08:46.360 --> 08:48.153
I wouldn't fucking vote for me.

08:48.153 --> 08:50.781
You did the right thing
addressing this head-on, ma'am.

08:50.781 --> 08:52.532
This is head-on?

08:52.532 --> 08:54.576
With someone's head on a spike

08:54.576 --> 08:56.536
is how I should have
addressed it.

08:56.536 --> 08:58.080
Where are we on the suspect?

08:58.080 --> 09:00.040
Intel expects to be
briefing you within the hour.

09:00.040 --> 09:01.667
[sighs]

09:01.667 --> 09:03.001
[woman] We couldn't wait
to comment on the incident

09:03.001 --> 09:04.461
until we had
someone in custody,

09:04.461 --> 09:06.129
not after the way
the debate ended.

09:06.129 --> 09:07.923
So instead,
you had me sit there

09:07.923 --> 09:09.675
with my tits hanging out,

09:09.675 --> 09:11.885
blathering for 15 minutes,
saying,

09:11.885 --> 09:15.138
"Trust me.
I am not always a fuck-up."

09:15.138 --> 09:16.598
I saw it.

09:16.598 --> 09:18.684
You came across as honest
and open, ma'am.

09:20.560 --> 09:22.980
Do you know who else
is honest and open?

09:24.398 --> 09:26.733
The person who says nothing

09:26.733 --> 09:29.569
when nobody asks
a fucking question!

09:32.364 --> 09:34.533
[Arjun]
I see politics never sleeps.

09:34.533 --> 09:35.993
Oh, please,

09:35.993 --> 09:38.203
tell me I'm just
having a bad dream.

09:38.203 --> 09:40.330
We just got
the new poll numbers.

09:40.330 --> 09:43.333
Do share.
The suspense is killing me.

09:45.043 --> 09:47.754
Gao is within three points.

09:49.006 --> 09:51.258
And that's taking into account
the speech?

09:52.676 --> 09:55.220
It could've been a lot worse.

09:55.220 --> 09:56.805
Get the fuck out,

09:56.805 --> 09:58.140
both of you.

10:03.061 --> 10:05.063
[sighs]

10:05.063 --> 10:06.273
[doorbell rings]

10:06.273 --> 10:08.191
Unless you need
something stiffer?

10:08.191 --> 10:09.818
How about cyanide?

10:09.818 --> 10:11.570
We only have hemlock.

10:11.570 --> 10:14.197
How poetic.

10:14.197 --> 10:18.243
Why did I let you talk me into
hiring those two idiots?

10:18.243 --> 10:20.037
Because they're the best
at what they do.

10:20.037 --> 10:22.205
Oh, I see.

10:22.205 --> 10:24.958
Then I'll start
packing up my office.

10:25.834 --> 10:27.169
Firing them
this close to the election

10:27.169 --> 10:28.295
will only do more harm.

10:28.962 --> 10:30.505
To whom?

10:30.505 --> 10:32.966
They just made me admit
I was weak.

10:33.800 --> 10:36.720
All you admitted was that
you're not infallible.

10:36.720 --> 10:39.514
In an election,
they're the same thing.

10:39.514 --> 10:41.224
What was I thinking?

10:41.224 --> 10:44.061
You got out in front of it
and you told the truth.

10:44.061 --> 10:46.396
It would've been better
not to say anything.

10:46.396 --> 10:47.564
Mm.

10:49.066 --> 10:51.818
- I think you're overreacting.
- Of course I am.

10:51.818 --> 10:53.862
Because I should have
not reacted at all.

10:53.862 --> 10:57.532
Now the public
can second-guess me.

10:57.532 --> 10:59.910
I should have
trusted my judgment.

10:59.910 --> 11:00.952
You were honest
with the people.

11:00.952 --> 11:02.412
There's no bad judgment there.

11:02.412 --> 11:03.914
Fucking stop it!

11:04.748 --> 11:06.249
If I did the right thing,

11:06.249 --> 11:08.460
then why is Nancy fucking Gao

11:08.460 --> 11:10.504
within three fucking points?

11:10.504 --> 11:12.297
I think your advisers
were right.

11:12.297 --> 11:14.049
Oh, I see.

11:14.049 --> 11:16.134
So when there's another Eros

11:16.134 --> 11:17.969
and our planet is burning,

11:17.969 --> 11:20.055
at least
we did the right thing.

11:20.055 --> 11:22.391
I don't like to see you
like this.

11:22.391 --> 11:24.643
♪ ♪

11:24.643 --> 11:26.937
You wanted to be a part
of this campaign.

11:26.937 --> 11:29.606
You're right.
I did.

11:29.606 --> 11:31.274
Now we know I'm not infallible.

11:32.901 --> 11:34.778
[glass bangs on table]

11:34.778 --> 11:36.738
[Adams] Marco Inaros killed
everyone on the Sojourner,

11:36.738 --> 11:39.199
disguised the ship,
and then used it to attack us.

11:39.199 --> 11:41.493
We stopped him this time.

11:41.493 --> 11:43.745
Our intel on the Inaros
faction is limited.

11:43.745 --> 11:45.956
They've been linked
to multiple acts of piracy,

11:45.956 --> 11:47.707
smuggling,
and extortion in the Belt

11:47.707 --> 11:50.627
but nothing on the scale
of Black Sky and Golden Bough.

11:50.627 --> 11:52.546
It appears Marco has
a very loyal following

11:52.546 --> 11:54.923
amongst his people,
but his group's politics

11:54.923 --> 11:56.591
and independent way
of operating

11:56.591 --> 11:57.926
have proved divisive

11:57.926 --> 11:59.845
even amongst
other OPA factions.

11:59.845 --> 12:01.888
[McCourt]
A public operation this large

12:01.888 --> 12:04.141
doesn't exactly fit
the faction's profile.

12:04.141 --> 12:06.643
How certain are we that
the OPA information is valid?

12:06.643 --> 12:08.812
We have high confidence
in our source.

12:08.812 --> 12:12.399
Marco Inaros is looking
to make a name for himself,

12:12.399 --> 12:14.776
and now he has.

12:14.776 --> 12:16.862
We've been digging
into Marco's whereabouts,

12:16.862 --> 12:18.738
and a deep-cover asset
in the Belt

12:18.738 --> 12:20.615
intercepted this broadcast.

12:21.533 --> 12:24.161
This was taken days ago
aboard the Pizzouza,

12:24.161 --> 12:25.954
a Belter freighter
out of Pallas Station.

12:25.954 --> 12:28.415
With the cooperation
of the governor of Ceres,

12:28.415 --> 12:30.250
we renditioned
a known associate of Marco

12:30.250 --> 12:32.544
to a black site
and confirmed the ID.

12:32.544 --> 12:34.212
Apparently,
Marco often travels

12:34.212 --> 12:36.089
on freighter ships
for anonymity.

12:36.089 --> 12:38.717
And uses passengers
as, uh, human shields.

12:38.717 --> 12:40.886
Real hero of the people.

12:40.886 --> 12:42.971
Is Marco still aboard
the freighter?

12:42.971 --> 12:44.973
We've been monitoring
the ship's flight path.

12:44.973 --> 12:46.349
It hasn't made any stops,

12:46.349 --> 12:47.684
and no other ships
have docked with it.

12:47.684 --> 12:49.144
Whoever got on
hasn't gotten off.

12:49.144 --> 12:50.604
But none of your assets
witnessed him

12:50.604 --> 12:52.147
actually board the ship?

12:52.147 --> 12:54.524
No, but as I said,
our confidence is high.

12:54.524 --> 12:56.943
Assuming he's still
on the ship,

12:56.943 --> 12:58.862
what are our options?

12:58.862 --> 13:01.323
[clears throat]

13:01.323 --> 13:03.867
The UNN Raskolnikov
is the closest battleship

13:03.867 --> 13:05.619
in the freighter's AO.

13:05.619 --> 13:08.038
On your order, the Raskolnikov
can destroy the freighter

13:08.038 --> 13:10.707
with a missile strike
in a matter of minutes.

13:10.707 --> 13:13.001
Marco and everyone else
on board will be eliminated.

13:14.294 --> 13:16.129
There better be another option.

13:17.464 --> 13:19.549
A tactical marine strike.

13:19.549 --> 13:22.135
The Raskolnikov will fire
a precision rail gun shot

13:22.135 --> 13:24.638
in order to take out
the ship's drive.

13:24.638 --> 13:26.473
Then a marine insertion team
in a breaching pod

13:26.473 --> 13:28.350
will board and take the ship.

13:28.350 --> 13:30.352
Collateral damage will be low,

13:30.352 --> 13:32.812
but our own risk of casualties
still exists.

13:32.812 --> 13:36.066
But is there a chance we would
be able to capture Marco alive?

13:36.066 --> 13:38.151
Yes, ma'am, but a very low one.

13:39.319 --> 13:41.321
[hologram chirps]

13:41.321 --> 13:44.157
If we could put
this terrorist on trial,

13:44.157 --> 13:46.201
we could make an example
out of him

13:46.201 --> 13:49.120
for any other Belters
looking to prey upon

13:49.120 --> 13:51.706
the colony ships
at the blockade.

13:51.706 --> 13:54.209
Keep monitoring the freighter.

13:54.209 --> 13:57.420
I want both strike options
on the table.

13:57.420 --> 14:00.215
General, move your team
into position

14:00.215 --> 14:01.800
and notify me
when they're ready.

14:01.800 --> 14:04.469
- Yes, ma'am.
- I'll make my decision then.

14:04.469 --> 14:11.476
♪ ♪

14:11.476 --> 14:12.936
[man] Okay, that's good.
Hold it there.

14:12.936 --> 14:14.688
[Murtry]
Captain Holden.

14:14.688 --> 14:17.148
Obviously, the predicament
that we're in down here

14:17.148 --> 14:18.692
and our ships are in up there

14:18.692 --> 14:20.360
wasn't something
that we could've planned for.

14:20.360 --> 14:22.320
No, but it would help
if your people

14:22.320 --> 14:24.447
shared some of your supplies
with the settlers.

14:24.447 --> 14:27.409
We don't know how long we're
going to survive down here,

14:27.409 --> 14:29.869
so I need to put the interests
of my people first.

14:29.869 --> 14:32.080
It's gonna be a lot shorter
for all of us

14:32.080 --> 14:33.832
if people begin to starve.

14:33.832 --> 14:35.375
I understand that,
which is why

14:35.375 --> 14:37.377
we all need to get out of here
as soon as possible.

14:39.754 --> 14:42.674
Has company policy
suddenly changed?

14:42.674 --> 14:44.968
In light of your
recent confession

14:44.968 --> 14:46.428
and the fusion problem,

14:46.428 --> 14:48.888
all our priorities
have changed.

14:48.888 --> 14:50.640
You said your ghost friend

14:50.640 --> 14:52.809
has been turning on
these ancient machines here?

14:52.809 --> 14:54.811
Yeah, and unless we can
shut them off,

14:54.811 --> 14:57.439
I don't think we'll get
our fusion drives back online.

14:57.439 --> 14:58.648
Is there anything
my people can do

14:58.648 --> 15:00.900
or...or...or help you do?

15:00.900 --> 15:02.694
- Like what?
- I don't know. I don't know.

15:02.694 --> 15:04.321
I'm just trying
to work out exactly

15:04.321 --> 15:06.948
what we're dealing with here
so that we can possibly

15:06.948 --> 15:10.243
help you fix the situation.

15:10.243 --> 15:12.454
Nobody wins if we all die.

15:12.454 --> 15:13.997
It's not up to me.

15:13.997 --> 15:15.498
Unless Miller comes back,

15:15.498 --> 15:18.084
I don't think
there's anything I can do.

15:18.084 --> 15:21.504
Mr. Holden.
Good, you're both here.

15:21.504 --> 15:23.131
- I have bad news.
- [Holden sighs]

15:23.131 --> 15:24.799
Seems to be contagious.

15:24.799 --> 15:27.010
It's not the only thing.

15:27.010 --> 15:28.845
Before we evacuated,

15:28.845 --> 15:31.097
I noticed some kind of...

15:31.097 --> 15:34.267
microorganism
growing in my eye.

15:34.267 --> 15:37.145
I've examined
nearly everyone here.

15:37.145 --> 15:38.897
We are all infected.

15:38.897 --> 15:40.273
I still need to check you.
Sit down.

15:40.273 --> 15:42.108
You told me
it was an allergy.

15:42.108 --> 15:43.526
That's what I've been
telling everyone.

15:43.526 --> 15:46.196
I...I don't want
to start a panic.

15:46.196 --> 15:48.490
The truth is,

15:48.490 --> 15:51.451
single-cell microorganisms

15:51.451 --> 15:53.036
native to this planet

15:53.036 --> 15:54.788
are making a home in our eyes.

15:54.788 --> 15:58.625
They're not hijacking our cells
like a virus would,

15:58.625 --> 16:01.294
but human bodies are water

16:01.294 --> 16:03.713
and high-energy molecules.

16:05.507 --> 16:07.842
None of their natural
competitors are in us.

16:07.842 --> 16:10.762
So our vitreous fluid
is a new environment

16:10.762 --> 16:13.014
that they are quite happy in...

16:13.014 --> 16:16.393
lots of little green babies
filling up the space.

16:16.393 --> 16:17.769
So th...they're...

16:17.769 --> 16:19.479
they're eating away
at our eyes?

16:19.479 --> 16:22.148
Yes, they probably will end up
eating away at our eyes.

16:22.148 --> 16:23.733
So what can you do?

16:23.733 --> 16:26.444
- Right now, nothing.
- [device chirps]

16:26.444 --> 16:28.947
Hmm.
Let me try again.

16:28.947 --> 16:31.241
- [device beeps]
[Murtry] So how long...

16:31.241 --> 16:32.992
until people start going blind?

16:32.992 --> 16:34.411
[Elvi] They already are.

16:34.411 --> 16:36.287
I can't be sure
until we all lose sight,

16:36.287 --> 16:38.081
but maybe a day.

16:38.081 --> 16:40.458
A day? That's all?

16:40.458 --> 16:42.210
Why is it suddenly
happening now?

16:42.210 --> 16:44.879
Well, these things
like saltwater.

16:44.879 --> 16:48.550
That flood probably acted like
a great, big exposure event.

16:48.550 --> 16:50.593
Also, we're all living
in each other's pockets,

16:50.593 --> 16:53.680
so everything is going
to spread more easily.

16:55.598 --> 16:58.643
Have you noticed
any kind of green spots

16:58.643 --> 17:00.729
or floaters in your eyes?

17:00.729 --> 17:02.605
No, not at all.
Why?

17:02.605 --> 17:05.108
You don't seem to be infected.

17:05.108 --> 17:08.403
Everyone's infected
but him?

17:09.738 --> 17:10.989
Does this maybe
have something to do

17:10.989 --> 17:12.574
with your alien ghost friend?

17:12.574 --> 17:13.867
It couldn't.

17:13.867 --> 17:16.161
It's only a transmission
in my head.

17:16.161 --> 17:17.912
I need a blood sample
from you.

17:17.912 --> 17:20.248
Doctor, I think it goes
without saying

17:20.248 --> 17:23.334
that curing this
is our main priority now.

17:23.334 --> 17:27.088
Um, all of our safety
depends on it.

17:27.088 --> 17:29.090
I'll do everything I can.

17:29.090 --> 17:35.847
♪ ♪

17:35.847 --> 17:38.266
Is it okay?
Thank you.

17:38.266 --> 17:41.770
[indistinct chatter]

17:41.770 --> 17:43.396
[woman coughs]

17:57.952 --> 18:00.205
Why you sitting
all by yourself?

18:00.205 --> 18:03.208
Me dad went looking
for me mom.

18:03.208 --> 18:06.336
- They never came back.
- Mm.

18:10.757 --> 18:13.802
That happened
to a bunch of people.

18:13.802 --> 18:15.887
Your parents made sure
you made it, though.

18:15.887 --> 18:18.306
Yeah, I guess so.

18:18.306 --> 18:19.933
That was their job,

18:19.933 --> 18:22.227
to protect you,
to make sure that you're safe.

18:24.062 --> 18:25.939
But they're not here anymore.

18:27.982 --> 18:29.818
No.

18:29.818 --> 18:31.236
No, they're not.

18:35.198 --> 18:36.950
What happened to your eyes?

18:36.950 --> 18:39.410
Green stuff got in them.

18:39.410 --> 18:42.372
Yeah, I've been seeing
green spots too.

18:42.372 --> 18:43.832
Does it hurt?

18:45.083 --> 18:46.459
Just itches.

18:49.671 --> 18:52.841
Hey, you see that pretty lady
over there?

18:52.841 --> 18:54.342
No, right there.

18:56.553 --> 18:58.346
Everything's green.

18:58.346 --> 19:05.353
♪ ♪

19:10.233 --> 19:11.734
[cup thunks on floor]

19:16.072 --> 19:19.200
Don't worry.
I'll see for the both of us.

19:19.200 --> 19:20.827
[Liam] Hey, what are you doing?

19:20.827 --> 19:22.495
[Angeletti] Hey, hey.
[Liam] Give me that!

19:22.495 --> 19:24.664
[Angeletti]
Oye, don't fucking touch me!

19:24.664 --> 19:27.667
- [overlapping shouting]
[Liam] Hey! Give me that back!

19:27.667 --> 19:29.586
Stay here.

19:29.586 --> 19:32.463
[shouting continues]

19:32.463 --> 19:34.048
[Angeletti]
Ka tinga stay over there!

19:34.048 --> 19:36.217
Oye, don't fucking touch me!

19:36.217 --> 19:37.677
- Fucking thief!
- I did not do nothing!

19:37.677 --> 19:38.970
[Eugene]
You tried to steal our water!

19:38.970 --> 19:39.846
I was going to get
my own wa...

19:39.846 --> 19:40.889
[blow lands]

19:40.889 --> 19:42.974
[Liam] You fucking liar!

19:42.974 --> 19:45.059
- Stand down!
- [overlapping shouting]

19:45.059 --> 19:47.395
Stand the fuck down!

19:48.980 --> 19:50.815
And get back to your post.
That's an order.

19:50.815 --> 19:52.066
Go.

19:53.902 --> 19:56.404
[indistinct chatter]

19:56.404 --> 19:59.407
Hey.
Come on.

19:59.407 --> 20:06.414
♪ ♪

20:15.131 --> 20:17.342
This is only the beginning.

20:17.342 --> 20:18.635
Yup.

20:23.723 --> 20:24.933
At some point,
you know we're gonna

20:24.933 --> 20:27.644
have to kill
some of these people.

20:27.644 --> 20:30.438
In things like this,
that's what always happens.

20:49.624 --> 20:50.959
- [electricity crackles]
- [hisses]

20:50.959 --> 20:52.627
[Naomi] Careful.
- Damn it.

20:52.627 --> 20:53.795
[Naomi] You're gonna need
every last one

20:53.795 --> 20:55.505
of those power modules.

20:55.505 --> 20:57.090
There should be 12 of them.

20:57.090 --> 20:58.883
Yeah, I see them.

20:58.883 --> 21:01.761
You ever been in the guts
of a ship like this before?

21:01.761 --> 21:03.179
[Felcia] Not a working one.

21:03.179 --> 21:04.514
[switch clicks]

21:04.514 --> 21:06.349
There was an old
decommissioned freighter

21:06.349 --> 21:08.685
on the Ganymede docks I went to
on a school field trip.

21:10.478 --> 21:13.314
I thought I'd be doing stuff
like this in university sims,

21:13.314 --> 21:15.149
not for real in orbit.

21:15.149 --> 21:17.151
Trust me,
this is a better education

21:17.151 --> 21:19.362
than any university
could give you.

21:19.362 --> 21:20.655
[chuckles]

21:20.655 --> 21:22.281
[Naomi] What's so funny?

21:22.281 --> 21:24.033
You sound like my mother.

21:24.033 --> 21:26.119
- [laughs softly]
- [machine part clanks]

21:26.119 --> 21:29.330
Well, she's right.

21:29.330 --> 21:31.416
For what it's worth,

21:31.416 --> 21:34.502
your mother hates herself
for what she did.

21:34.502 --> 21:37.046
I don't believe she ever
wanted to hurt anyone.

21:37.046 --> 21:41.843
She was just trying to protect
your family and your home.

21:41.843 --> 21:45.263
Ilus is her dream, not mine.

21:45.263 --> 21:47.932
I know the feeling
of wanting to run away.

21:47.932 --> 21:50.268
Every day
is harder than the next.

21:52.020 --> 21:54.188
What did you do?

21:56.482 --> 21:58.860
I ran...

21:58.860 --> 22:01.904
and regretted it ever since.

22:01.904 --> 22:03.573
- [part clicks]
- Your mother's been caring

22:03.573 --> 22:06.534
for you even since
before you were born.

22:06.534 --> 22:08.077
[part clanks]

22:08.077 --> 22:11.080
She wants you to go
and chase your dreams.

22:11.080 --> 22:14.042
That's all any mother
ever wants.

22:15.585 --> 22:17.503
But she's scared

22:17.503 --> 22:20.048
that you'll make a mistake,

22:20.048 --> 22:23.843
do something you'll regret,

22:23.843 --> 22:26.137
she won't be able
to protect you.

22:27.388 --> 22:29.015
[sighs heavily]

22:29.015 --> 22:30.933
None of that
really matters anymore.

22:30.933 --> 22:33.061
[part clanks]

22:33.061 --> 22:39.442
♪ ♪

22:39.442 --> 22:40.985
We need to get

22:40.985 --> 22:43.738
all of the sedatives
and painkillers

22:43.738 --> 22:46.074
from the first aid kits
in the camp.

22:46.074 --> 22:47.909
That'll help
with the blindness?

22:47.909 --> 22:49.202
In a way.

22:50.161 --> 22:53.164
When people realize
they can't see anymore,

22:53.164 --> 22:55.249
saying "keep calm and carry on"

22:55.249 --> 22:56.834
is probably
not going to be enough.

22:56.834 --> 22:58.503
You don't think you'll find
a treatment before then?

22:58.503 --> 23:00.004
[needle squelches]

23:00.004 --> 23:01.631
Not unless I can find
the reason that...

23:01.631 --> 23:04.467
- you seem to be immune.
- [computer dings]

23:04.467 --> 23:06.302
Well, not everybody
got the plague.

23:06.302 --> 23:08.971
Not everybody
talks to an alien.

23:08.971 --> 23:11.599
Going blind doesn't sound
as bad anymore.

23:11.599 --> 23:13.976
[screen chirping]

23:15.645 --> 23:18.064
You make it sound
like a burden.

23:18.064 --> 23:19.273
If you need a guy
talking to me,

23:19.273 --> 23:21.526
you'd feel the same way.

23:21.526 --> 23:24.278
I don't think I would.
[laughs softly]

23:24.278 --> 23:26.656
You are being given
knowledge and answers

23:26.656 --> 23:28.658
that humans have only
dreamt about.

23:29.617 --> 23:31.869
I've also been given
horrific nightmares

23:31.869 --> 23:35.665
and visions of death
I can never unsee.

23:35.665 --> 23:39.127
To me, that sounds like
an acceptable trade-off.

23:39.127 --> 23:41.587
I have traveled
billions of kilometers

23:41.587 --> 23:44.507
to be the first exobiologist
to study...

23:44.507 --> 23:47.343
the most basic forms
of extraterrestrial life,

23:47.343 --> 23:49.095
and you, on the other hand,

23:49.095 --> 23:51.931
are the only person
in human history

23:51.931 --> 23:55.726
with a direct line
of communication

23:55.726 --> 23:59.355
to an advanced alien species,
and you're annoyed?

24:01.107 --> 24:04.110
It's not the same
when you don't have the choice.

24:06.904 --> 24:09.323
Any scientist would kill

24:09.323 --> 24:12.160
to change places with you.

24:12.160 --> 24:14.078
I know I would.

24:14.078 --> 24:21.085
♪ ♪

24:21.085 --> 24:22.503
[sighs]

24:25.965 --> 24:27.925
How are the Belters
holding up?

24:27.925 --> 24:30.178
They're not all gonna make it.

24:30.178 --> 24:32.847
That's not the optimism
I was hoping for.

24:35.057 --> 24:37.602
I'm taking some of the meds
out of your first aid kit.

24:37.602 --> 24:39.604
Are you sick?

24:39.604 --> 24:40.938
No.

24:40.938 --> 24:42.773
But everyone else is.

24:42.773 --> 24:45.693
[indistinct chatter]

24:45.693 --> 24:48.237
Hey, you been seeing
green spots in your eyes?

24:49.530 --> 24:51.657
Yeah. Why?

24:51.657 --> 24:53.492
Everyone's been infected
with them but me

24:53.492 --> 24:55.244
for some reason.

24:55.244 --> 24:57.205
The doctor lady said
it was allergies.

25:00.041 --> 25:02.251
♪ ♪

25:02.251 --> 25:04.420
[whispering]
It's much worse.

25:04.420 --> 25:05.922
How much worse?

25:07.965 --> 25:10.968
We got maybe a day
before everyone goes blind.

25:15.223 --> 25:16.641
[whispering]
Are you fucking serious?

25:19.894 --> 25:21.312
[exhales]

25:21.312 --> 25:23.356
A lot more of us
aren't gonna make it now.

25:23.356 --> 25:25.066
We're working on a treatment,

25:25.066 --> 25:27.068
so hopefully,
that doesn't happen.

25:27.068 --> 25:29.195
But if people start panicking,

25:29.195 --> 25:32.657
none of us are gonna
make it out of here alive.

25:32.657 --> 25:35.785
I need your help making sure
everyone stays calm.

25:40.373 --> 25:42.291
I can't do this without you.

25:44.835 --> 25:46.254
Yeah, I'll do what I can.

25:46.254 --> 25:53.261
♪ ♪

25:58.766 --> 26:02.144
[Arjun] "Great Hector's sister
did Achilles win,

26:02.144 --> 26:04.021
but our great Ajax

26:04.021 --> 26:07.149
bravely beat down him."

26:07.149 --> 26:11.028
Achilles was
the greatest of warriors,

26:11.028 --> 26:14.740
so Ulysses tries to bend
and defeat him

26:14.740 --> 26:17.368
with reverse psychology.

26:17.368 --> 26:19.704
Now, this technique may seem...

26:19.704 --> 26:20.663
[knock at door]

26:24.792 --> 26:27.336
Sit, sit.
Pay attention.

26:27.336 --> 26:29.338
I'm not going to be
on the test.

26:29.338 --> 26:31.007
[soft scattered laughter]

26:31.007 --> 26:32.842
I have a feeling
whatever I say next

26:32.842 --> 26:34.427
will be nowhere near
as interesting

26:34.427 --> 26:36.846
as our guest's entrance.

26:36.846 --> 26:38.764
- [soft scattered laughter]
[woman] That's true.

26:38.764 --> 26:41.058
[Arjun] Finish the play...
that will be on the test,

26:41.058 --> 26:43.227
as well as
the readings of Preston,

26:43.227 --> 26:44.937
Wordsworth, and Logan.

26:44.937 --> 26:46.564
I will see all of you
next week.

26:49.859 --> 26:51.193
[sighs]

26:52.236 --> 26:54.530
I thought surprise visits
were against the rules.

26:54.530 --> 26:56.490
Fuck the rules.
I'm in charge.

26:56.490 --> 26:58.117
And I wanted to see
my husband.

26:58.117 --> 27:00.536
Well, I'm flattered
to be a security breach,

27:00.536 --> 27:02.788
but what is so urgent?

27:02.788 --> 27:04.999
I'm sorry.

27:04.999 --> 27:07.626
I was overstressed
and not myself this morning.

27:09.712 --> 27:13.716
Well, I was wondering
who that woman on our sofa was,

27:13.716 --> 27:16.552
the woman who didn't even want
this job in the first place.

27:17.595 --> 27:20.389
[Avasarala]
You're right. I never did.

27:20.389 --> 27:23.100
I blame it on the goddamn Ring.

27:23.100 --> 27:24.560
When Eros happened,

27:24.560 --> 27:27.521
I remember I felt so helpless.

27:28.773 --> 27:30.441
Everything was about to end,

27:30.441 --> 27:33.486
and there was nothing
I could do about it.

27:33.486 --> 27:35.571
That's how
I'm feeling right now.

27:35.571 --> 27:37.990
Because you're scared
for the planet

27:37.990 --> 27:40.368
or because you're not
in control of the outcome?

27:40.368 --> 27:43.120
Both of those things.

27:43.120 --> 27:46.499
I wish I could do more
to help you.

27:46.499 --> 27:49.710
I could never do this job
without you.

27:49.710 --> 27:53.714
I need to lean on you
during times like this.

27:53.714 --> 27:58.177
♪ ♪

27:58.177 --> 28:00.971
I've never questioned
the things you've done before

28:00.971 --> 28:03.140
because I knew you were
doing them

28:03.140 --> 28:05.518
for the right reasons.

28:05.518 --> 28:07.520
But it feels like

28:07.520 --> 28:09.480
this election

28:09.480 --> 28:12.191
isn't about you
being right anymore.

28:12.191 --> 28:14.652
It's just about you

28:14.652 --> 28:16.320
needing to win.

28:17.696 --> 28:19.949
Would losing be so bad?

28:22.576 --> 28:24.537
I don't know,

28:24.537 --> 28:26.330
which is what scares me,

28:26.330 --> 28:28.916
and why I need to win.

28:28.916 --> 28:31.043
I can't be right if I don't.

28:32.711 --> 28:35.005
How far are you willing
to go to find out?

28:36.382 --> 28:38.384
As far as I have to.

28:38.384 --> 28:44.890
♪ ♪

28:53.858 --> 28:57.069
[footsteps approaching]

28:57.069 --> 28:58.988
[Alex] Oh, hey.

28:58.988 --> 29:01.490
I just wanted to tell you
Naomi and Felcia,

29:01.490 --> 29:03.117
they got an extra three hours
of power

29:03.117 --> 29:04.827
out of the light shuttle.

29:09.248 --> 29:11.417
They're real pretty, huh?

29:11.417 --> 29:13.335
They remind me of Ganymede.

29:13.335 --> 29:15.379
The guy who put them in
is from there.

29:15.379 --> 29:18.257
He actually went back there
to help, you know, rebuild.

29:18.257 --> 29:20.676
Ganymede was so beautiful.

29:22.219 --> 29:24.263
When Felcia was little,
she'd make me take her

29:24.263 --> 29:27.016
to look at the mirrors
above the domes.

29:27.016 --> 29:29.518
I thought
she liked them because...

29:29.518 --> 29:31.520
[laughs softly]
...they were big and shiny.

29:31.520 --> 29:33.105
[laughs softly]

29:33.105 --> 29:35.733
[Lucia] But she wanted
to figure out how they worked.

29:35.733 --> 29:37.902
I don't remember
ever seeing her happier

29:37.902 --> 29:40.696
than those moments
staring up into the sky.

29:46.994 --> 29:48.829
That was a different lifetime.

29:51.874 --> 29:54.084
I had a family back on Mars.

29:54.084 --> 29:56.170
What happened to them?

29:56.170 --> 29:57.755
Oh, no, I mean...

29:57.755 --> 29:59.215
No, they're...they're...
they're still back there

29:59.215 --> 30:00.216
and everything.

30:00.216 --> 30:01.675
It's just, uh...

30:01.675 --> 30:03.385
I'm just not
part of it anymore.

30:06.972 --> 30:10.434
[machine beeps, whooshes]

30:10.434 --> 30:13.145
When my son was five,

30:13.145 --> 30:15.397
the little guy, he wanted sand
for his birthday.

30:15.397 --> 30:17.107
- Sand?
[Alex] Mm-hmm.

30:17.107 --> 30:20.486
Sand from a real beach
from Earth.

30:20.486 --> 30:21.987
[laughs softly]

30:23.822 --> 30:25.533
He must have seen it
in some picture somewhere.

30:25.533 --> 30:27.451
You...you have any idea
how much that costs

30:27.451 --> 30:28.619
to get that stuff?

30:28.619 --> 30:30.246
[laughs softly]

30:30.246 --> 30:31.789
I still remember
the look on his face

30:31.789 --> 30:33.707
when he opened that box.

30:33.707 --> 30:36.001
♪ ♪

30:36.001 --> 30:37.253
[inhales deeply]

30:37.253 --> 30:39.088
I wonder if he still has that.

30:43.175 --> 30:45.928
I lost my family...

30:45.928 --> 30:47.763
because I couldn't be the man
that my wife

30:47.763 --> 30:50.516
and my little kid
needed me to be.

30:50.516 --> 30:52.268
I have to live with that.

30:52.268 --> 30:54.478
I can never make that right.

30:55.896 --> 30:58.190
You still have a chance
to make it right,

30:58.190 --> 30:59.733
make new memories with your kid

30:59.733 --> 31:01.569
instead of sitting around
like me,

31:01.569 --> 31:04.280
hanging on to one moment
that I got right.

31:04.280 --> 31:07.241
♪ ♪

31:07.241 --> 31:10.119
They're fixing Ganymede and...

31:10.119 --> 31:13.497
those busted mirrors right now.

31:13.497 --> 31:15.124
There's hope for you.

31:17.042 --> 31:19.128
The mirrors,

31:19.128 --> 31:20.254
that's the answer.

31:21.839 --> 31:24.800
I think I know
how to save the Barb.

31:24.800 --> 31:28.512
One time, Felcia and I
saw a tug drone go out

31:28.512 --> 31:30.931
and manually raise a mirror
when the thrusters failed.

31:30.931 --> 31:32.516
Right, okay.
I see what you're getting at.

31:32.516 --> 31:34.310
And yes, the Roci has drones,

31:34.310 --> 31:36.729
but even if we used them all,
there's no way we'd increase

31:36.729 --> 31:38.522
the speed of a ship
like the Barb enough.

31:38.522 --> 31:41.483
But we could use
the Roci itself, right?

31:41.483 --> 31:43.694
We'd be putting
both ships at risk.

31:43.694 --> 31:45.738
But could it work?

31:45.738 --> 31:48.282
[sighs softly]

31:48.282 --> 31:51.577
In principle, it could work.

31:51.577 --> 31:52.953
We've got enough battery power

31:52.953 --> 31:54.622
for the thrust
it would require,

31:54.622 --> 31:56.582
but we'd still need something
to connect the ships,

31:56.582 --> 31:59.043
and there's nothing
on the Roci we could use.

31:59.043 --> 32:00.919
What about mining nets?

32:00.919 --> 32:02.880
- We have some on the Barb.
[Alex] Yeah, I don't know.

32:02.880 --> 32:04.965
For this not to be suicide,

32:04.965 --> 32:06.216
we gotta have some distance
between us.

32:06.216 --> 32:07.760
How much distance?

32:07.760 --> 32:10.012
[sighs]
Kilometer to be safe.

32:10.012 --> 32:13.849
Okay, so what if we
take the nets apart

32:13.849 --> 32:16.769
and weave together
a single cable that long?

32:16.769 --> 32:18.103
Could that work?

32:19.980 --> 32:22.441
Please?

32:22.441 --> 32:25.277
I need to make this right.

32:25.277 --> 32:27.279
Naomi, what's the...

32:29.198 --> 32:30.908
I said
I don't wanna talk to you.

32:30.908 --> 32:34.036
Just listen, Felcia.
Please.

32:34.036 --> 32:36.747
Your mom has got an idea
on how to save the Barb.

32:36.747 --> 32:39.166
Wait, she does?

32:39.166 --> 32:40.793
Mm-hmm.

32:43.921 --> 32:46.632
We want to connect
the Roci to the Barb

32:46.632 --> 32:50.344
so the Roci can pull the ship
higher up into orbit.

32:50.344 --> 32:52.638
We're going to need you
to deconstruct the mining nets

32:52.638 --> 32:54.682
and weld
and weave them together

32:54.682 --> 32:57.559
into a single tow cable.

32:57.559 --> 32:59.520
Yeah.
Yeah, we can do that.

32:59.520 --> 33:01.438
The cable will need
to be at least

33:01.438 --> 33:04.400
one kilometer long for safety.

33:04.400 --> 33:06.694
We can't have the ships
running into each other.

33:07.736 --> 33:09.613
And we can't connect it
to the nose.

33:09.613 --> 33:11.156
Our center of mass has changed

33:11.156 --> 33:12.825
because of all the lithium
we're carrying.

33:12.825 --> 33:14.910
We'll need to build a gantry
to provide a height

33:14.910 --> 33:17.162
to counterbalance everything.

33:17.162 --> 33:19.123
It could work, but...

33:19.123 --> 33:21.041
do we have enough time
to do all this?

33:21.041 --> 33:23.544
We're going to find out.

33:25.337 --> 33:32.344
♪ ♪

33:34.012 --> 33:35.180
[Wei] Blind?

33:35.180 --> 33:36.724
You're fucking joking, right?

33:36.724 --> 33:39.518
She's working on a treatment,
so there's hope.

33:39.518 --> 33:41.019
But obviously,
things have changed.

33:41.019 --> 33:43.021
We need to maintain peace
with the Belters

33:43.021 --> 33:44.857
until we know Dr. Okoye
can treat us,

33:44.857 --> 33:47.359
and that means we're gonna need
to share our food and water.

33:47.359 --> 33:49.820
That's why you stopped
the fight.

33:49.820 --> 33:53.907
This thing could go sideways
very easily,

33:53.907 --> 33:56.827
get us all killed
if we don't think quick.

33:56.827 --> 33:58.829
But if we do this right,

33:58.829 --> 34:00.914
this disaster
is the best thing

34:00.914 --> 34:02.750
that could've
happened to us.

34:02.750 --> 34:06.670
It did in one day what was
gonna take us years.

34:06.670 --> 34:09.715
If we wait out these settlers,

34:09.715 --> 34:10.883
this planet's ours.

34:10.883 --> 34:12.259
You heard what Holden said.

34:12.259 --> 34:13.677
He's gonna defend
the Belters' claim to--

34:13.677 --> 34:14.762
Which is why I'm not
putting my fate

34:14.762 --> 34:16.430
in the hands of a court.

34:16.430 --> 34:19.141
We have to silence
Holden now.

34:19.141 --> 34:20.267
[footsteps approaching]

34:20.267 --> 34:21.894
You seen Liam?

34:21.894 --> 34:24.229
He's on water purification duty
until further notice.

34:24.229 --> 34:26.315
Penance for overreaction.

34:31.653 --> 34:34.823
I've been thinking
about the "Anteros."

34:35.574 --> 34:39.036
I still have nightmares
about that ship,

34:39.036 --> 34:42.873
all those...
floating Belter faces.

34:44.166 --> 34:46.668
On the ride home,
I strapped myself to the wall

34:46.668 --> 34:49.671
when I slept to see if I could
forget about zero-G.

34:49.671 --> 34:51.715
But it didn't matter.

34:51.715 --> 34:53.717
Didn't sleep anyways.

34:54.802 --> 34:58.388
The RCE tripled
their profits that quarter,

34:58.388 --> 35:01.016
and I got an extra $6,000.

35:02.184 --> 35:04.102
I've been spilling blood
my entire career

35:04.102 --> 35:06.313
and making others rich off it.

35:07.606 --> 35:09.900
UN sent us to this planet

35:09.900 --> 35:12.820
to do research and to coexist
with the Belters,

35:12.820 --> 35:15.614
but it's in
the company's interests

35:15.614 --> 35:17.783
if the Belters eventually
cede their claim

35:17.783 --> 35:19.326
and any stake in the planet.

35:19.326 --> 35:21.995
My contract will give me
one percent

35:21.995 --> 35:23.330
of the claim value

35:23.330 --> 35:25.123
after all the Belters
have gone.

35:25.123 --> 35:28.085
Now, that meant millions
in lithium money.

35:28.085 --> 35:29.503
But if we can control

35:29.503 --> 35:31.171
the technology
that Holden activated,

35:31.171 --> 35:34.508
this planet is worth
hundreds of billions more.

35:34.508 --> 35:36.468
Sounds like you're finally
getting what you're owed.

35:36.468 --> 35:38.053
No, we're getting
what we're owed.

35:38.053 --> 35:40.514
There's more than enough
for the both of us...

35:40.514 --> 35:44.726
and for everyone who helps us
do what needs to be done.

35:45.769 --> 35:49.523
Things aren't going to end well
on this planet for Holden.

35:49.523 --> 35:51.567
And I need to know
that you've got my back

35:51.567 --> 35:53.318
when I make my move.

35:53.318 --> 35:55.445
You've never had to pay
for my loyalty.

35:55.445 --> 35:57.531
I thought so too,

35:57.531 --> 35:59.491
but your off-duty activities
have given me reason

35:59.491 --> 36:02.286
to question you.

36:02.286 --> 36:04.913
Amos is not a problem.

36:07.124 --> 36:08.458
Liam!

36:08.458 --> 36:12.129
[indistinct chatter]

36:12.129 --> 36:14.673
Liam, where are you?

36:14.673 --> 36:17.676
[water rushing]

36:19.678 --> 36:21.054
Liam!

36:26.351 --> 36:27.394
Liam?

36:27.394 --> 36:29.605
[ominous music]

36:29.605 --> 36:31.106
Liam?

36:31.106 --> 36:33.734
Liam! Liam!

36:33.734 --> 36:38.739
♪ ♪

36:38.739 --> 36:41.742
[tense music]

36:41.742 --> 36:47.956
♪ ♪

36:47.956 --> 36:50.125
Everybody stay the fuck back!

36:50.125 --> 36:51.585
- [people screaming]
- Stay the fuck back!

36:51.585 --> 36:53.378
What...what are you doing?
What are you doing?

36:53.378 --> 36:55.547
Come on! Stay back!

36:55.547 --> 36:57.424
- Just...
- Stay back!

36:57.424 --> 36:58.800
No, get...
Let me go!

36:58.800 --> 37:01.386
What are you doing?

37:01.386 --> 37:04.014
Shut the fuck up!

37:04.014 --> 37:05.891
Aah!

37:05.891 --> 37:07.267
You killed my friend,

37:07.267 --> 37:09.770
you fucking
piece-of-shit skinny!

37:09.770 --> 37:12.481
How does that feel?
How the fuck does that feel?

37:13.732 --> 37:15.317
- [Holden] Let him go!
- [Murtry] Let him go, Eugene!

37:15.317 --> 37:16.568
This guy killed
my best friend!

37:16.568 --> 37:17.694
Then he'll be dealt with.

37:17.694 --> 37:19.071
[Amos] He dies, you die.

37:19.071 --> 37:20.322
[Holden]
You got three seconds. One...

37:20.322 --> 37:21.531
Do it, I can't
protect you like this.

37:21.531 --> 37:22.824
Two...

37:22.824 --> 37:23.825
[Murtry]
Put your fucking gun down,

37:23.825 --> 37:25.369
or I'll shoot you myself!

37:29.498 --> 37:31.541
[gasping]

37:31.541 --> 37:33.335
What the fuck?

37:33.335 --> 37:36.254
[dark music]

37:36.254 --> 37:38.006
♪ ♪

37:38.006 --> 37:40.550
[groaning]

37:42.386 --> 37:46.848
[gasping]

37:52.521 --> 37:56.108
[people exclaiming]

38:01.905 --> 38:02.906
Ugh.

38:05.075 --> 38:08.704
♪ ♪

38:08.704 --> 38:10.497
What the fuck?

38:10.497 --> 38:12.666
♪ ♪

38:12.666 --> 38:16.795
[gasping]

38:16.795 --> 38:20.007
[groaning]

38:20.007 --> 38:21.800
[Murtry]
No, don't...don't touch him!

38:23.802 --> 38:25.429
What the fuck is happening?

38:25.429 --> 38:28.056
Those slugs...
they killed them.

38:30.767 --> 38:31.893
Where are they coming from?

38:36.481 --> 38:38.859
[people gasping]

38:38.859 --> 38:45.866
♪ ♪

38:57.461 --> 38:58.837
Everywhere.

38:58.837 --> 39:03.759
♪ ♪

39:03.759 --> 39:06.553
Any kind of change
in flight path?

39:06.553 --> 39:10.557
No, ma'am. The Pizzouza's
still on its same course.

39:10.557 --> 39:14.019
The UNN Raskolnikov
is ready, in position.

39:14.019 --> 39:16.605
Missiles are hot.
Rail gun is charged.

39:16.605 --> 39:18.398
And your marines?

39:18.398 --> 39:21.610
UNMC 1 is floating dark
in the Pizzouza's flight path.

39:21.610 --> 39:23.445
Both strike options are ready.

39:23.445 --> 39:26.448
[indistinct radio chatter]

39:26.448 --> 39:29.951
[woman 1]
Shields at 100%.

39:29.951 --> 39:31.787
[woman 2]
Standing by.

39:36.416 --> 39:38.752
Send in your marines, General.

39:38.752 --> 39:41.379
Yes, ma'am.

39:41.379 --> 39:44.007
Raskolnikov,
breaching option is a go.

39:44.007 --> 39:47.010
[dramatic music]

39:47.010 --> 39:54.017
♪ ♪

40:01.525 --> 40:04.528
[whooshing]

40:11.952 --> 40:14.955
[clanking]

40:17.207 --> 40:20.210
[indistinct radio chatter]

40:21.962 --> 40:24.965
[radio chatter continues]

40:29.136 --> 40:31.471
[marine 1] Left.
One left. One left.

40:31.471 --> 40:33.807
[marine 2] Hey, you, you!
Out where we can see you!

40:33.807 --> 40:35.976
[marine 3]
Where is Marco Inaros?

40:35.976 --> 40:38.478
Mi na sasa. Mi na sasa.
Mi na sasa.

40:38.478 --> 40:40.480
[marine 1] Going east.
Going east. Keep moving.

40:40.480 --> 40:44.067
[marine 3] Keep moving.
Marco Inaros. Marco Inaros!

40:44.067 --> 40:45.318
[woman]
We don't know!

40:45.318 --> 40:46.736
[marine 1]
Clear!

40:46.736 --> 40:49.406
Clear. Clear.

40:50.740 --> 40:51.867
Clear.

40:54.161 --> 40:56.413
[marine 3]
No IDs. Clear.

40:56.413 --> 40:59.666
[indistinct yelling]

41:01.084 --> 41:02.669
[marine 2]
Crew quarters clear!

41:02.669 --> 41:04.045
[woman]
Mi na sasa!

41:04.045 --> 41:05.380
What's happening?

41:05.380 --> 41:07.549
Do they have control
of the ship?

41:07.549 --> 41:11.136
They're moving to OPS.
Another 30 seconds.

41:12.470 --> 41:14.472
[marine 1]
Cover right. Cover right.

41:14.472 --> 41:17.309
[marine 3]
Clear right!

41:17.309 --> 41:20.187
Stop moving!
Where is Marco Inaros?

41:20.187 --> 41:21.479
- I don't know!
- [marine 3] Where is he?

41:21.479 --> 41:23.523
Where is Marco Inaros?

41:23.523 --> 41:26.109
[marine 3]
No IDs. Continue sweep.

41:26.109 --> 41:28.153
[woman]
Mi na sasa. Mi na sasa.

41:28.153 --> 41:29.738
I don't know.

41:29.738 --> 41:31.156
[marine 3]
Contact right!

41:31.156 --> 41:33.825
[gunfire]

41:33.825 --> 41:35.410
[indistinct yelling]

41:35.410 --> 41:38.205
[marine 1]
Return fire! Return fire!

41:38.205 --> 41:39.915
[marine 3]
Oh, my God! We're under fire!

41:43.835 --> 41:48.423
♪ ♪

41:48.423 --> 41:51.426
[alarm beeping]

41:56.514 --> 41:58.767
[man]
This is UNMC 1.

41:58.767 --> 42:00.393
The Pizzouza...

42:00.393 --> 42:01.770
it's gone.

42:01.770 --> 42:08.777
♪ ♪
